This paper is about image inpainting using deep neural networks, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves training a structure reconstructor and a texture generator, which requires the use of machine learning techniques (cs.AI, cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of appearance flow, which is a technique commonly used in graphics and visualization (cs.GR). Finally, the experiments involve multiple publicly available datasets, which suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM).
